  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 72-year-old man presents with progressive dyspnea and decreased breath sounds at the right base. Point-of-care ultrasound is shown. The patient is positioned sitting upright with arms resting on the bedside table for thoracentesis. What is the most appropriate needle insertion site for ultrasound-guided thoracentesis?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Posterior axillary line 1–2 intercostal spaces below the upper margin of the effusion"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Midclavicular line at the 6th intercostal space"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Anterior axillary line at the level of the nipple"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Paravertebral line at the 10th intercostal space"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Midaxillary line below the 8th intercostal space"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">posterior</a> axillary line 1–2 <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-section-id=\"OxcI9e0\" data-sememe-id=\"rh0f2f\">intercostal spaces</a> below the upper margin of the effusion is a safe needle insertion site for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-sememe-id=\"fK0kfS\">ultrasound</a>-guided <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a>. Puncture <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zad8f9786872edfa102f7204c82b56244\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zad8f9786872edfa102f7204c82b56244\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">lateral</a> to the midscapular line reduces the risk of injuring the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z900b0459efed171b6183dbbbb2da52b9\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z900b0459efed171b6183dbbbb2da52b9\" data-section-id=\"PvcWZe0\" data-sememe-id=\"PscWEd0\">intercostal artery</a>, while targeting a level below the visible upper margin places the needle firmly within the fluid collection and away from the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ap0QLS&anker=Zbc4e2cd5b038bc04fba483dc59b22270\" data-learningcard-id=\"ap0QLS\" data-anker=\"Zbc4e2cd5b038bc04fba483dc59b22270\" data-section-id=\"OvcIZe0\">lung parenchyma</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z27547ca50784fdbb5a6c42f2967aa90d\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z27547ca50784fdbb5a6c42f2967aa90d\" data-section-id=\"PvcWZe0\" data-sememe-id=\"y-Xd-00\">midclavicular line</a> is too <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z611d380c96ce797875c8e46c949415ed\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z611d380c96ce797875c8e46c949415ed\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">anterior</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z7461aaa50eeae708c4dba8bf8b41d291\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z7461aaa50eeae708c4dba8bf8b41d291\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">medial</a> for safe <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a>. This location increases the risk of injury to the intercostal vessels and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ap0QLS&anker=Zbc4e2cd5b038bc04fba483dc59b22270\" data-learningcard-id=\"ap0QLS\" data-anker=\"Zbc4e2cd5b038bc04fba483dc59b22270\" data-section-id=\"OvcIZe0\">lung parenchyma</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>The <span data-sememe-id=\"3RWS5O0\">anterior axillary line</span> at the level of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=B60zMS&anker=Zeb39c4d9794319c5a38ee3d9d589cad5\" data-learningcard-id=\"B60zMS\" data-anker=\"Zeb39c4d9794319c5a38ee3d9d589cad5\" data-section-id=\"eEcxuV0\" data-sememe-id=\"BPXzSy\">nipple</a> is too <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z611d380c96ce797875c8e46c949415ed\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z611d380c96ce797875c8e46c949415ed\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">anterior</a> and potentially too high for optimal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Op0IpS&anker=Za7b4bc1601743ad1327ca3052deb2089\" data-learningcard-id=\"Op0IpS\" data-anker=\"Za7b4bc1601743ad1327ca3052deb2089\" data-section-id=\"bCcHqe0\" data-sememe-id=\"sNXtcA\">pleural fluid</a> access. This approach does not follow the recommended anatomical landmarks for safe <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a> and may not provide adequate access to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=F50gNg&anker=Z4f6cc81490f80454657181033c0f0214\" data-learningcard-id=\"F50gNg\" data-anker=\"Z4f6cc81490f80454657181033c0f0214\" data-sememe-id=\"1o02aS\">pleural effusion</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>The paravertebral line at the 10th <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-section-id=\"OxcI9e0\" data-sememe-id=\"rh0f2f\">intercostal space</a> is too <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">posterior</a> and too low. This location significantly increases the risk of injury to abdominal organs including the diaphragm, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=P60WOS&anker=Zbeb0bf4bb898a5c4899f2e6b499eeec2\" data-learningcard-id=\"P60WOS\" data-anker=\"Zbeb0bf4bb898a5c4899f2e6b499eeec2\">spleen</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>While the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z39059ba3e8199b4d77488ad72fba4a96\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z39059ba3e8199b4d77488ad72fba4a96\" data-section-id=\"PvcWZe0\" data-sememe-id=\"aZcQZa0\">midaxillary line</a> is an acceptable <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Zad8f9786872edfa102f7204c82b56244\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Zad8f9786872edfa102f7204c82b56244\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">lateral</a> approach, entry below the 8th <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-section-id=\"OxcI9e0\" data-sememe-id=\"rh0f2f\">intercostal space</a> increases the risk of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_P05hT&anker=Z2c9dff1d80514e6feecc76a04a352b11\" data-learningcard-id=\"_P05hT\" data-anker=\"Z2c9dff1d80514e6feecc76a04a352b11\" data-section-id=\"p8XLn-\" data-sememe-id=\"upaprl\">injury to the diaphragm</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=P60WOS&anker=Zbeb0bf4bb898a5c4899f2e6b499eeec2\" data-learningcard-id=\"P60WOS\" data-anker=\"Zbeb0bf4bb898a5c4899f2e6b499eeec2\">spleen</a>, and should be avoided.</div>",
