    {
      "text": "A 67-year-old patient with a history of heart failure presents with worsening dyspnea. Point-of-care ultrasound is shown. Informed consent is obtained for the indicated ultrasound-guided therapeutic procedure. The patient is ambulatory and can follow instructions. What is the most appropriate choice of patient positioning, probe type, and probe orientation for this procedure?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Position patient prone with pillow under chest, use linear probe in longitudinal orientation"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Position patient sitting with arms on bedside table, use high-frequency linear array transducer in B-mode"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Position patient supine with head elevated 30 degrees, use phased array transducer in Doppler mode"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Position patient in reverse Trendelenburg with arms at sides, use curvilinear probe in B-mode"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Position patient in lateral decubitus with right side down, use curvilinear probe in M-mode"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tg0XC2&anker=Z423422a74e138fb64d0150221926a76c\" data-learningcard-id=\"tg0XC2\" data-anker=\"Z423422a74e138fb64d0150221926a76c\" data-section-id=\"7O14FS0\" data-sememe-id=\"yobdeu\">Prone positioning</a> would make access to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Op0IpS&anker=Z4b59d3c6136a1b8cdd58e52df726845f\" data-learningcard-id=\"Op0IpS\" data-anker=\"Z4b59d3c6136a1b8cdd58e52df726845f\" data-section-id=\"bCcHqe0\" data-sememe-id=\"bkXHmy\">pleural space</a> extremely difficult and is not a standard approach for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a>. This position would also compromise patient comfort and safety during the procedure.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- The sitting position with arms resting on a bedside table is the standard positioning for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a>, allowing optimal access and using gravity to pool <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Op0IpS&anker=Za7b4bc1601743ad1327ca3052deb2089\" data-learningcard-id=\"Op0IpS\" data-anker=\"Za7b4bc1601743ad1327ca3052deb2089\" data-section-id=\"bCcHqe0\" data-sememe-id=\"sNXtcA\">pleural fluid</a> in dependent areas. A high-frequency <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=S70yOh&anker=Zce005fa15aa5e44ba0f381064d71291a\" data-learningcard-id=\"S70yOh\" data-anker=\"Zce005fa15aa5e44ba0f381064d71291a\" data-section-id=\"8s1O9R0\" data-sememe-id=\"13W2hO0\">linear array transducer</a> in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z227fa5a411686bfd445a97578737a6ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z227fa5a411686bfd445a97578737a6ad\" data-section-id=\"EPX8gy\">B-mode</a> is the recommended probe choice for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-sememe-id=\"fK0kfS\">ultrasound</a>-guided <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a> to identify the puncture site and mark the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a>. This setup allows for the best visualization of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Za466a64a9ff741e0365c57cc1db2aa1b\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Za466a64a9ff741e0365c57cc1db2aa1b\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">superficial</a> structures and precise needle guidance.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z406d8c98eb82ea3bac3abd1dc5c6243e\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z406d8c98eb82ea3bac3abd1dc5c6243e\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\" data-sememe-id=\"AobReu\">Supine positioning</a> with head elevation is not optimal for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a> because it does not allow gravity to pool <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Op0IpS&anker=Za7b4bc1601743ad1327ca3052deb2089\" data-learningcard-id=\"Op0IpS\" data-anker=\"Za7b4bc1601743ad1327ca3052deb2089\" data-section-id=\"bCcHqe0\" data-sememe-id=\"sNXtcA\">pleural fluid</a> in dependent areas. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=S70yOh&anker=Z5b26487c96a94e4c4a7565b28cd27b16\" data-learningcard-id=\"S70yOh\" data-anker=\"Z5b26487c96a94e4c4a7565b28cd27b16\" data-section-id=\"8s1O9R0\" data-sememe-id=\"d3WohO0\">Phased array transducers</a> have small footprints suitable for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-section-id=\"OxcI9e0\" data-sememe-id=\"rh0f2f\">intercostal spaces</a> but are not the standard choice for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Reverse <span data-sememe-id=\"_kc5qc0\">Trendelenburg positioning</span> is not a standard position for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a> and would not optimize fluid pooling. While a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=S70yOh&anker=Z83999871bad97988b751868bfa22007b\" data-learningcard-id=\"S70yOh\" data-anker=\"Z83999871bad97988b751868bfa22007b\" data-section-id=\"8s1O9R0\" data-sememe-id=\"W3WPhO0\">curvilinear probe</a> can be used, the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=S70yOh&anker=Zce005fa15aa5e44ba0f381064d71291a\" data-learningcard-id=\"S70yOh\" data-anker=\"Zce005fa15aa5e44ba0f381064d71291a\" data-section-id=\"8s1O9R0\" data-sememe-id=\"13W2hO0\">linear array transducer</a> is preferred for the high-resolution imaging needed for procedural guidance.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>While <span data-sememe-id=\"5nWiFN0\">lateral decubitus positioning</span> can be used if the patient cannot tolerate sitting, it is not the first choice if the patient can sit upright. Additionally, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z74ac643f57640474360cc12e3e942088\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z74ac643f57640474360cc12e3e942088\" data-section-id=\"EPX8gy\">M-mode</a> is not the primary imaging mode for identifying puncture sites during <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a> procedures.</div>",
