      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vh0Aff&anker=Z173ea3cc1a02a887b8543c256fb768ff\" data-learningcard-id=\"vh0Aff\" data-anker=\"Z173ea3cc1a02a887b8543c256fb768ff\" data-sememe-id=\"Bk0zJT\">Pneumothorax</a> can cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=eo0xaS&anker=Zcda47ad2f9d1107fac48126410f29c8c\" data-learningcard-id=\"eo0xaS\" data-anker=\"Zcda47ad2f9d1107fac48126410f29c8c\">acute chest pain</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Xq09CS&anker=Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-learningcard-id=\"Xq09CS\" data-anker=\"Zec7af3634c75f9e5227d266d823e5ea7\" data-sememe-id=\"KaYUln\">dyspnea</a>, but the specific constellation of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a>, chest discomfort, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZI0ZYh&anker=Z11178ec3c2e582d07f19c0f784e018a3\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZI0ZYh\" data-anker=\"Z11178ec3c2e582d07f19c0f784e018a3\" data-section-id=\"5h1ieg0\" data-sememe-id=\"GT0BH2\">hypoxia</a> occurring after large volume fluid removal is more consistent with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=F50gNg&anker=Z9c9f7290cce668ad1cb399e8c2124115\" data-learningcard-id=\"F50gNg\" data-anker=\"Z9c9f7290cce668ad1cb399e8c2124115\" data-section-id=\"-AaDmM\" data-sememe-id=\"ibaJtQ\">reexpansion pulmonary edema</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=F50gNg&anker=Z9c9f7290cce668ad1cb399e8c2124115\" data-learningcard-id=\"F50gNg\" data-anker=\"Z9c9f7290cce668ad1cb399e8c2124115\" data-section-id=\"-AaDmM\" data-sememe-id=\"ibaJtQ\">Reexpansion pulmonary edema</a> is a recognized complication of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zce29ab17413907ca15f2d60e38a65bd4\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zce29ab17413907ca15f2d60e38a65bd4\" data-section-id=\"i6WJkm0\" data-sememe-id=\"rwcf4e0\">therapeutic thoracentesis</a> that occurs after rapid reexpansion of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ap0QLS&anker=Zbc4e2cd5b038bc04fba483dc59b22270\" data-learningcard-id=\"ap0QLS\" data-anker=\"Zbc4e2cd5b038bc04fba483dc59b22270\" data-section-id=\"OvcIZe0\">lung tissue</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-section-id=\"FfWgLk0\" data-sememe-id=\"b31HSg0\">Risk factors</a> include large volume removal (&gt; 1.5 L). The classic presentation includes <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a>, chest discomfort, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZI0ZYh&anker=Z11178ec3c2e582d07f19c0f784e018a3\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZI0ZYh\" data-anker=\"Z11178ec3c2e582d07f19c0f784e018a3\" data-section-id=\"5h1ieg0\" data-sememe-id=\"GT0BH2\">hypoxia</a> that develop during or immediately after the procedure.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=F50gNg&anker=Zd5d9fbbb82bb6501ad7d33a91fc9ce6b\" data-learningcard-id=\"F50gNg\" data-anker=\"Zd5d9fbbb82bb6501ad7d33a91fc9ce6b\" data-section-id=\"IJ1Yv30\" data-sememe-id=\"d_boMw\">Pleuritis</a> typically develops over hours to days after <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a>, not immediately. The acute onset of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a>, chest discomfort, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZI0ZYh&anker=Z11178ec3c2e582d07f19c0f784e018a3\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZI0ZYh\" data-anker=\"Z11178ec3c2e582d07f19c0f784e018a3\" data-section-id=\"5h1ieg0\" data-sememe-id=\"GT0BH2\">hypoxia</a> occurring directly after large volume fluid removal suggests a mechanical rather than infectious etiology.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=F50gNg&anker=Zdf67280592b889d4f0c8e49adddf581a\" data-learningcard-id=\"F50gNg\" data-anker=\"Zdf67280592b889d4f0c8e49adddf581a\" data-section-id=\"1i12qg0\" data-sememe-id=\"7B04Xi\">Hemothorax</a> from vascular injury typically manifests with <span data-sememe-id=\"3LdSxq0\">hemodynamic instability</span> and signs of blood loss. The timing of symptoms immediately after large volume removal and the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=3L0Sxg&anker=Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\" data-learningcard-id=\"3L0Sxg\" data-anker=\"Z53178f74af701c6933574f4f111d6391\">cough</a> with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZI0ZYh&anker=Z11178ec3c2e582d07f19c0f784e018a3\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZI0ZYh\" data-anker=\"Z11178ec3c2e582d07f19c0f784e018a3\" data-section-id=\"5h1ieg0\" data-sememe-id=\"GT0BH2\">hypoxia</a> are not characteristic of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=F50gNg&anker=Zdf67280592b889d4f0c8e49adddf581a\" data-learningcard-id=\"F50gNg\" data-anker=\"Zdf67280592b889d4f0c8e49adddf581a\" data-section-id=\"1i12qg0\" data-sememe-id=\"7B04Xi\">hemothorax</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=F50gNg&anker=Z54df3018267c30fdb3852a4a190b1b0d\" data-learningcard-id=\"F50gNg\" data-anker=\"Z54df3018267c30fdb3852a4a190b1b0d\" data-section-id=\"N31-ig0\" data-sememe-id=\"WSbPAG\">Pleural empyema</a> is an infectious complication that develops over days, not immediately following <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a>. The immediate onset of symptoms after large volume drainage indicates a mechanical rather than infectious complication.</div>",
