    {
      "text": "A patient presents with dyspnea and a large right-sided pleural effusion extending from the 4th to the 10th intercostal space on ultrasound. The patient is positioned sitting upright with arms on the bedside table. Using ultrasound guidance, where should the needle be inserted for therapeutic thoracentesis?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "5th intercostal space at the midscapular line"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "8th intercostal space at the midclavicular line"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "9th intercostal space at the posterior axillary line"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "10th intercostal space at the midscapular line"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "6th intercostal space at the posterior axillary line"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 5,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>The 5th <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-section-id=\"OxcI9e0\" data-sememe-id=\"rh0f2f\">intercostal space</a> is at the level of the upper margin of the effusion. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">Thoracentesis</a> should ideally be performed 1–2 <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-section-id=\"OxcI9e0\" data-sememe-id=\"rh0f2f\">intercostal spaces</a> below the upper margin of the effusion to ensure adequate fluid access while ensuring safety.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>The 8th <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-section-id=\"OxcI9e0\" data-sememe-id=\"rh0f2f\">intercostal space</a> is appropriate for depth, but the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z27547ca50784fdbb5a6c42f2967aa90d\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z27547ca50784fdbb5a6c42f2967aa90d\" data-section-id=\"PvcWZe0\" data-sememe-id=\"y-Xd-00\">midclavicular line</a> is not a recommended anatomical landmark for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a>. The procedure should be performed at the midscapular or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">posterior</a> axillary line to avoid vascular injury.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">posterior</a> axillary line is an appropriate landmark for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=tt0X23&anker=Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-learningcard-id=\"tt0X23\" data-anker=\"Zf8c6a207291e79a303cd2b3ab3e2c338\" data-sememe-id=\"cTYapo\">thoracentesis</a>, but the needle should not be inserted below the 8th <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-section-id=\"OxcI9e0\" data-sememe-id=\"rh0f2f\">intercostal space</a> to minimize the risk of intraabdominal organ injury.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>The 10th <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-section-id=\"OxcI9e0\" data-sememe-id=\"rh0f2f\">intercostal space</a> is well below the safe insertion zone and significantly increases the risk of intraabdominal injury. Additionally, this location is at the lower margin of the effusion rather than in an optimal position for fluid drainage.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) CORRECT:</h4>Correct -- The needle should be inserted 1–2 <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-section-id=\"OxcI9e0\" data-sememe-id=\"rh0f2f\">intercostal spaces</a> beneath the upper margin of the effusion, which would be the 5th or 6th <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=0p0eLS&anker=Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-learningcard-id=\"0p0eLS\" data-anker=\"Z91784abdd53ef71f6ef7580f565a82ad\" data-section-id=\"OxcI9e0\" data-sememe-id=\"rh0f2f\">intercostal space</a> in this patient. The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Z917870fa18c05b025cc3696075936299\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">posterior</a> axillary line is an appropriate anatomical landmark that avoids injury to intercostal vessels while providing safe access to the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Op0IpS&anker=Z4b59d3c6136a1b8cdd58e52df726845f\" data-learningcard-id=\"Op0IpS\" data-anker=\"Z4b59d3c6136a1b8cdd58e52df726845f\" data-section-id=\"bCcHqe0\" data-sememe-id=\"bkXHmy\">pleural space</a> for fluid drainage.</div>",
